      "role": "user",
      "content": "confirmation bias? i dont know.. it didnt feel like my brain playing tricks on me. it was too precise. like the lighting on the road hit the car at the exact same angle every time too. and the driver didnt even look up when he passed the second and third time. it felt way too synchronized to be a coincidence. it actually felt like the world just... paused and reloaded. do you think that's even possible? like if reality actually isn't what we think it is?",
