      "content": "wormholes? maybe... but it didn't feel like a whole different universe. it felt more like a technical error. like the simulation we're in just hit a snag and had to repeat a few lines of code. i've been reading about simulation theory and some people say \"glitches\" like this are actually evidence that we're living in a programmed environment. if that's true, why would these things happen to me specifically? does it mean the system is starting to break down?",
